.TH IITJ-LOGIN 1 "March 2026" "iitj-login 4.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
iitj-login \- keep IIT Jodhpur hostel Ethernet logged into the FortiGate captive portal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B iitj-login
.I command
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B iitj-login
is a background login helper for the IIT Jodhpur hostel LAN.
It keeps an Ethernet session authenticated by detecting captive portal interception
and re-submitting IITJ LDAP credentials before the session expires.
.PP
The installer also applies the practical fixes needed for this network on real
machines, including MAC randomization handling, Docker subnet conflict detection,
gateway hostname pinning, and portal route correction.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B install
Run the setup wizard.
This detects the active Ethernet interface, applies network fixes, stores
credentials, or lets you keep existing stored credentials during a reinstall,
installs the background service, and installs this man page on
supported systems.
.TP
.B uninstall
Remove the background service, stored application data, and installed man page.
.TP
.B login
Run the login loop in the foreground.
This command is mainly intended for the installed service.
.TP
.B start
Start the background service.
.TP
.B stop
Stop the background service.
.TP
.B status
Show service status output.
.TP
.B version
Print the current binary version.
.SH INSTALL FLOW
The normal install path is:
.IP "1." 4
Install the binary with the bootstrap script or build it from source.
.IP "2." 4
Run
.B iitj-login install
once.
.IP "3." 4
Use
.B iitj-login status
to verify that the service is running.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/iitj-login/
Default Linux data directory.
Contains encrypted credentials and runtime configuration.
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/iitj-login.service
Linux systemd user unit installed by
.BR iitj-login\ install .
.SH SECURITY
Credentials are stored locally using AES-256-GCM encryption.
No external service is involved other than the IITJ captive portal itself.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Install and configure:
.B iitj-login install
.TP
Check service state:
.B iitj-login status
.TP
Show version:
.B iitj-login version
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR launchctl (1)
